                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="49950" author="pjones" created="Fri, 4 Jan 2013 10:53:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Landed for 2.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="47512" author="bergwolf" created="Wed, 7 Nov 2012 02:21:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;One more is submitted for review:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/4487&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/4487&lt;/a&gt; llite: don&apos;t release nd-&amp;gt;path in ll_follow_link&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="46893" author="bergwolf" created="Wed, 24 Oct 2012 23:03:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Following patches were submitted to gerrit:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/3755&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/3755&lt;/a&gt;    kernel: v3.5 defines INVALID_UID&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/3756&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/3756&lt;/a&gt;    llite: kernel 3.5 renames end_writeback to clear_inode&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/3757&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/3757&lt;/a&gt;    kernel: 3.5 kernel encode_fh passes in parent inode&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/4384&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/4384&lt;/a&gt;    kernel: 3.4 kmap_atomic has one argument&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/4385&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/4385&lt;/a&gt;    kernel: kernel 3.6 changes i_dentry/d_alias to hlist&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/4386&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/4386&lt;/a&gt;    kernel: 3.6 dentry_open uses struct path as first arg&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/4387&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/4387&lt;/a&gt;    llite: atomic_open support&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;They still depend on patches for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1337&quot; title=&quot;Client support for 3.3 Linux kernels&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1337&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-1337&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; due to conflicts in lustre_core.m4 file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To pass sanity in 3.6 kernel, following bugfix patches are also needed (plus patches from &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1337&quot; title=&quot;Client support for 3.3 Linux kernels&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1337&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-1337&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;):&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,4039&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,4039&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,4078&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,4078&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,4079&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,4079&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,4091&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,4091&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="46860" author="bergwolf" created="Tue, 23 Oct 2012 06:19:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have 7 patches queued for 3.6 support and will submit for review soon.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
